"title": "7438: sanctuary",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7438: sanctuary",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A place or structure set aside for the worship of God. In Scripture the word generally refers to the tabernacle or the Jerusalem temple. By extension the word signifies a location or spiritual state providing refuge from hostile forces, human, spiritual or natural.</p>\n<h2>The tabernacle</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8-Exod25:9\">EXO 25:8–25:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:1\">EXO 36:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:2\">HEB 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:5\">HEB 8:5</a></p>\n<h3>Worship in the tabernacle was divinely ordained in great detail</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7-Exod30:10\">EXO 30:7–30:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:37-Lev7:38\">LEV 7:37–7:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:44\">LEV 23:44</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:1\">EXO 39:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:30-Num3:31\">NUM 3:30–3:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:1\">HEB 9:1</a></p>\n<h3>The people gave generously for the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:4-Exod36:5\">EXO 36:4–36:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Approach to God's sanctuary was strictly regulated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:4\">LEV 12:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:21-Lev21:23\">LEV 21:21–21:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:10\">NUM 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:38\">NUM 3:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:19\">NUM 8:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:5\">NUM 18:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:20\">NUM 19:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:18\">2CH 26:18</a></p>\n<h3>A reverent attitude was commanded</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:30\">LEV 19:30</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:2\">LEV 26:2</a></p>\n<h2>The Jerusalem temple</h2>\n<h3>David made extensive preparations for Solomon to build the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:17-1Chr22:19\">1CH 22:17–22:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:2-1Chr28:3\">1CH 28:2–28:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:6\">1CH 28:6</a></p>\n<h3>The inner sanctuary of the temple corresponded to the Most Holy Place in the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:19\">1KI 6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:6\">1KI 8:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:7\">2CH 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:49\">1CH 6:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:1-Heb9:4\">HEB 9:1–9:4</a></p>\n<h2>Some places were considered sacred because of God's presence and activity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:17\">EXO 15:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:16-Gen28:17\">GEN 28:16–28:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:1-Exod3:5\">EXO 3:1–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps15:1\">PSA 15:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:2\">PSA 63:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:16-Ps73:17\">PSA 73:16–73:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:12\">JER 17:12</a></p>\n<h2>Conduct that displeases God will lead to a nation's sanctuaries being destroyed</h2>\n<h3>Disobedience to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:31\">LEV 26:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:8\">2CH 30:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:24\">EZK 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:7\">LAM 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:9\">AMO 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:11\">MAL 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Dishonesty in dealings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:18\">EZK 28:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Idolatry</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:3\">LEV 20:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek8:6\">EZK 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:38-Ezek23:39\">EZK 23:38–23:39</a></p>\n<h3>Profaning the sanctuary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:7-Ezek44:8\">EZK 44:7–44:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:4\">ZEP 3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Sanctuary from vengeance: the cities of refuge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh20:2-Josh20:3\">JOS 20:2–20:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:6\">NUM 35:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:9-Num35:12\">NUM 35:9–35:12</a></p>\n<h2>God himself is his people's sanctuary</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:20\">PSA 31:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:27\">DEU 33:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:7-Ps17:9\">PSA 17:7–17:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:1\">PSA 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:7\">PSA 32:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:1\">PSA 46:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:1-Ps64:2\">PSA 64:1–64:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:4\">PSA 91:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:4\">ISA 25:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:16\">EZK 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:7\">PHP 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19\">HEB 6:19</a></p>\n<h2>Non-material ``sanctuaries'' of God</h2>\n<h3>Heaven, where God is perfectly worshipped</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:19\">PSA 102:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>God's worshipping people, in whom God dwells</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps114:2\">PSA 114:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">1CO 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:21\">EPH 2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:5\">1PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ himself as the ``place'' where God dwelt on earth</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:19-John2:21\">JHN 2:19–2:21</a></p>",
